Zarath nstra (Zoroaster) taught that earth water and fire were excellent creatures of Ahura-Mazda (Ormuzd). and that they must not be polluted by contact with a (lead body. Cremation and interment were therefore out of the question. The bodies of the dead were to be placed on 3 very elevated spot, specially prepared, where carnivorous birds and dogs could see them, and they were to be fastened down by the feet and hair that their bones might not be carried to water or earth hy birds or dogs. Cf. Avesta‚ Vendz‘dad V¹ 93-4·

The Towers ofSilence, the well-known cemetery of the Parsee community at Bombay, situated on the highest point of Malabar Hill, with groves hard by that swarm with vultures, mark a modern survival of the rite referred to in the text.
